<br>
Watch a Beastlord or Wizard zone/port with their warder/familiar out. As soon as they poof, so does the pet.<br>
<br>
Balanz has it right, though. Because of the BUFF Icon, the server records that (save on zone), and when you pop into the new zone, it 'remakes' a new pet with when it layers that buff icon back into it's proper place. Now, with our pets, that would mean that it would autogenerate a new pet, new name, etc. In order to save the current pet, buffs, stats and all, one would have to save that pet into a database table, and reload that pet into the new zone. The cost to VI? More than it's worth to the game play.<br>
<br>
I'm more pissed that VI's rep makes such a stupid and poor sighted claim as to state it's somehow balanced that beastlords suffer this penalty for the benefit of escaping with their pet. For all I care, let the pet die if it's engaged in combat, I could care less. It would anyways, once left alone in an appropriately leveled zone.<br>
<br>
Besides, what &quot;penalty&quot; do other clases suffer for zoning to escape? Oh, wait.. none.<br>
<br>
