<br>
Losing our second character when we zone is part of our class balance.  Barring <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Necromancers</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for the moment, no one else has a second character close to ours without having two PCs and two accounts.<br>
<br>
Suppose we <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>could</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> zone with our pets.  Assuming I can avoid petdeath, linkdeath, gating or teleport, I could <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>twink</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> a maxed out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and have him tag along with me all day.  Besides a pair of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gnoll Hide Lariats</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I could supply him with a set of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dexterity</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> jewelry <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (I could carry the stackable components and make it myself)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as well as purchased or farmed melee gear with AC and statistics.<br>
<br>
Now I have a persistant <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ubaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and in so far as I could manage to keep him alive, I would rock until I logged out ten hours later.<br>
<br>
I am <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> nearly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> certain, based on what I think I know, that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Warders</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do not actually persist across zoning, but that a new one is automatically summoned.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Beastlords</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>essentially</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> lose their pet when zoning, having to spend time and mana rebuilding them.<br>
<br>
And I did not claim that <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>every</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> NPC would be able to zone if real pet zoning code were implemented, but that <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>some</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> might.  I do understand how models work, but there are a lot of global models, including PC races and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and adjacent zones often share some models <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (Giants, Gryphons, Gnolls)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I do not feel as if I need zoning pets, and think it would be a bad idea.<br>
