<br>
But again, that is the price we pay for having a nearly constant second character.<br>
<br>
I have <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>never</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> felt the need for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> root, snare, fear, charm, mezz, stun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or any means of escape which we do not <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>already</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> possess.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, when he is available, is our first line of defense against a hostile world.  He may <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> root</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> stun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If he is busy, or has left the mundane plane, there is:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Speed</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, in many forms: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> JBoots, TBoots, Innate Running Speed, Horse, Spirit of the Wolf, Wolf Blood Potions</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and, as was sung about a certain <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Jungle Man</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;When he gets in a scrape he makes his escape with the help of his friend a spell named</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Gate!&quot;<br>
<br>
This requires that you develop your channelling skill, and pay some attention to things like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dodge, AC, Agility, Hit Points, Stamina</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Channelling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  But then, survivability is one of the joys of being <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>human</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  I cannot count the number of times I have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gated</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> out from multiple foes.<br>
<br>
In so far as there is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>any</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> actual need for an additional escape means for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I would prefer to see it in the form of something like an improved <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rage of Zomm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, some kind of instant, short term, high taunt pet that could hold the enemy at bay long enough to flee.  That at least would be consistant with the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> theme.<br>
<br>
I do have some items in my inventory that cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Root</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Snare</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (I think), but I never needed to use them.  I strongly believe that a competent <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> requires neither <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> root, snare, fear, charm, mezz,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> stun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
